Hey What is Software?
-----

Processing data


I) Variable / Data type

1. What is Variable?
	
	> Its like a container to store the information or value or data.

Whole data, Decimal data, Dinesh Kumar, true/false, 'a'
INTEGER      FLOAT          STRING       BOOLEAN     CHARACTER

2. What is Data type?

	Defines the type of data to be stored in the variable.

Water(data) --> Bucket (Variable) --> Platic / Iron/ Aluminum (data type)

Head set (Data) --> Pouch (Variable) --> Leadher / Plastic (DT)


Data types classification:-
---------

1. PRIMITIVE (8)

	Define the range

	I) Numerical type

		a. Integral type - byte, short, int, long
		b. Floating type - float, double
		c. Character type - char

	II) Boolean type
		a. boolean type - boolean

Numbers...

-2^(n-1) to 2^(n-1) -1 

n - number of bits 

byte - 1 Byte - 8 bits - -128 to 127
short - 2 Byte - 16 bits - -32768 to 32767
int - 4 Byte - 32 bits - -2147483648 to 2147483647
long - 8 Byte - 64 bits -  -922337203 6854775808 to  922337203 6854775807

Decimal...

float - 4 Byte - 32 bits

after dot 7 digit

double - 8 Byte - 64 bits

after dot 15 digit

-------

char - 2 Byte - 16 bits

Sigle digit

boolean - N/A (1 bit)

true or false

2. NON-PRIMITIVE

	Not able to define the range

STRING
INTERFACe
CLASS
ENUM
OBJECT etc...


/*

byte, short, int, long -> 0
float, double -> 0.0
char --> \u0000
boolean --> false
String --> null

*/


Data type

name, size, range, default value.
